import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['Date'], data['CO2'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the trend of CO2 concentration over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['CO2'] = pd.to_numeric(data['CO2'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['CO2'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('CO2 concentration (ppm)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['Year'] = data['Date'].dt.year
    data = data.groupby('Year').mean().reset_index()
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.bar(data['Year'], data['CO2'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average CO2 concentration per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
